did.abstract: A collection of about 470 zines, mostly of the personal nature, mostly written by women, acquired during the period of the late 1990s to early 2000s.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Lisa Jaronski, aka, Lazy Jane, is from upstate New York. She is the author of the zines When Swinging Next to You, and Jurm, as well as a few single-issue zines.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Accessions described in this finding aid: 2013-0037

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Researchers must register and agree to copyright and privacy laws before using this collection.
All or portions of this collection may be housed off-site in Duke University's Library Service Center. The library may require up to 48-hours to retrieve these materials for research use.
Please contact Research Services staff before visiting the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library to use this collection.

scopecontent.head: Collection Overview
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of zines primarily from the U.S., with a small number from Canada, Australia, and New Zealand. Many of the zines were acquired through trade and larger organized swaps referred to as “Lazy Jane’s Zine Trades” arranged by the collector (ie: send in 30 copies of your zine, get 30 unique zines back from the other participants).

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is divided into two series: Zines by Women and Zines by Men, each of which is organized alphabetically by zine title.

acqinfo.head: Provenance
acqinfo.p: The Lisa Jaronski Zine Collection was acquired by the Rubenstein Library as a gift in 2013.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: The copyright interests in this collection have not been transferred to Duke University. For more information, consult the copyright section of the Regulations and Procedures of the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library.
